news.title: Chandigarh administration says 'won't go ahead' with 2008 housing scheme
news.para: The UT has also decided to refund the money deposited by the petitioners and the other applicants, as per an affidavit submitted by the UT with the HC.

news.title: Haryana cabinet approves land ownership policy for four villages in Hisar
news.para: The residents who have raised construction on an area of up to 250 square yards of land will be granted ownership rights after paying a fee of Rs 2000 per square yard.

news.title: We will continue to grow in Bengaluru & three other cities: Aravind Maiya, Embassy REIT
news.para: Embassy REIT anticipates strong growth in commercial real estate in India, with a focus on cities like Bangalore and plans to enter Chennai. They expect NOI to exceed Rs 3,000 crore in FY24 and have seen positive demand from global capitals for office space.  Plus, they are constructing close to 7 million square feet in our existing parks where the land is already paid for.

news.title: MIDC orders Indiabulls Real Estate to vacate 2,500 acres land in Nashik
news.para: Indiabulls Real Estate had in August 2007 entered into a share purchase agreement with MIDC which allowed its subsidiary Indiabulls Industrial Infrastructure to enter into lease deeds with MIDC on approximately 2,500 acres of land.

news.title: Extend rent act to buildings on port trust land to prevent eviction: Maharashtra LA speaker
news.para: Narwekar met MPA chairman Rajeev Jalota recently and gave directions to the body to not issue any eviction notice or take coercive action against tenants living in buildings on MPA land between Colaba and Wadala.

news.title: Godrej Properties buys 6.46 acres land parcel in Noida
news.para: Spread over about 6.46 acres, the land is located in Sector 44 and will offer approximately 1.4 million sq ft of development potential and an estimated revenue potential of about Rs 3,000 crore, said Godrej Properties.

news.title: MMRDA & SRA ink agreement to develop Ramabai Nagar slum pocket in Ghatkopar
news.para: A MMRDA official stated, "This agreement paves the way for the seamless progress of the project, with surveys scheduled to begin shortly to assess eligibility."

news.title: Upfront cost on property registration goes up in Karnataka
news.para: Currently, the stamp duty in Bangalore is 6.6% of the property's market value. The advance stamp duty will be adjusted against this at the time of the registration of the property. For resale, there is no impact as property registration often happens in a month.

news.title: Haryana RERA chairman meets builders over project delays, disputes
news.para: The authority, in a meeting with the developers on Monday evening, reiterated that completing delayed and stuck projects was its top priority and it will work with all stakeholders to ensure that these projects are delivered.

news.title: NCLT rejects Vistra ITCL’s plea to include additional claim in Satra Properties insolvency
news.para: The National Company Law Tribunal dismissed Vistra ITCL's application to include its additional claim in the resolution process of Satra Properties.

news.title: DLF in talks to buy projects coming up at Aerocity in Delhi
news.para: DLF is in discussions with Bharti Realty to acquire under-construction phases of Aerocity in Delhi. Brookfield acquired a controlling stake in Rostrum Realty.

news.title: Yamuna Expressway authority approves layouts of 600 plots, issues OCs to 1,200 flats
news.para: The Authority also approved the layout for nearly 600 plots in SDS Infracon township in Sector 26 A. SDS Infracon launched the township project in 2010 with over 1,400 plots.

news.title: Gurugram: ULB department seeks report on eight builders' offer to buy revenue road parcels
news.para: Revenue roads were originally carved out as paths to agricultural fields in village areas. They automatically came under the jurisdiction of the municipal corporations concerned after licensed colonies were developed.

news.title: China Vanke assures it can repay $630 million dollar bond amid liquidity worries
news.para: China's No.2 property developer by sales said in a statement to Reuters that the repayment process for the bond was "orderly". Shares of the company and prices of its 2029 dollar bonds recovered slightly after the statement.

news.title: A Vietnamese property tycoon accused of embezzling $12.5 billion begins her trial
news.para: The 66-year-old chair of the real estate company Van Thinh Phat allegedly used "thousands of ghost companies," paid bribes to government officials and violated banking regulations, according to a government document.

news.title: Country Garden lenders' group hires advisers for debt revamp talks: Sources
news.para: The hiring by the lenders' group comes as the Foshan-based developer, China's top private property company by sales, prepares to face a Hong Kong court on May 17 after a creditor filed a liquidation petition against it.

news.title: China's premier vows more support for property market stuck in the doldrums
news.para: The property sector has lurched from one crisis to another since 2021 after a regulatory crackdown on high leverage among developers triggered a liquidity crisis.

news.title: IWG posts 34% rise in profit in 2023
news.para: Landlords have seen gradual growth in office space utilisation since mid-2023 as tenants wind back pandemic-linked remote working arrangements and employees switch to a hybrid-work model requiring presence in the office several days a week.
